<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="543" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1395,1926]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1791,1817]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Baker, 1924)" authorityName="Vilbaste" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[663,982,1791,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Watanabella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montivaga">
<emphasis box="[663,817,1792,1817]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">W. montivaga</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, C. F." box="[832,974,1791,1817]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543" pagination="367" refId="ref2938" refString="Baker, C. F. (1924) Nomenclatorial notes on the Jassoidea, [II]. Philippine Journal of Science, 24, 367." type="journal article" year="1924">Baker, 1924</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by the shape of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="543" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1395,1926]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1863,1889]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name is a modification of the Latin word “ 
<emphasis box="[999,1083,1864,1889]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">curvam</emphasis>
” (curved), referring to the male pygofer side with a curved process on the inner side.
</paragraph>
